Article.ArticleTitle: [Searching for cytostatic substances in plant tissue of Maytenus molina by in vitro culture. III. Release of substances from active biological fractions from the callus extract of Maytenus wallichiana R. and B].

AbstractText: Chromatographic studies controlled by biological evaluation (Tetrahymena test) showed some colour substances among them tingenone and beta-sitosterol. In order to identify the substances extraction and biologically controlled chromatography was carried out. Two substances were isolated, their properties corresponding with tingenone and beta-sitosterol.
